<paragraph blockId="9.[212,1172,1283,1689]" lastBlockId="10.[144,1104,1376,1687]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="1844" pageId="9" pageNumber="1843">
Unguis of normal shape, without lateral or inner teeth. Unguiculus about half as long as unguis. Tibiotarsi with additional setae on all legs, some setae thickened (
<figureCitation box="[220,338,1665,1689]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[144,211,1210,1232]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1178]" captionTargetId="figure-153@10.[144,1104,168,1178]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 5. Aggressopygus sibiricus sp. nov.: (A,B) furca, anterior (A) and lateral (B) views; (C) maxillary head; (D) tibiotarsus 3; (E,F) labrum, variation; (G) anterior part of the head; (H) apical row of labral setae, ventral view; (I) anterior side of manubrium, specimen from mountainous Shoria." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5195067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5195067/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1843">Figure 5D</figureCitation>
). Tibiotarsal tenent setae short and pointed. Spurs X and B 
<quantity box="[1024,1067,1665,1689]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="9" pageNumber="1843" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
Leg 3 of adult males (
<specimenCount box="[295,461,1376,1400]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1844" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
studied) much thinner and shorter than other setae on tibiotarsi. Ventral tube with 5 + 5 laterodistal and with 4 posterior setae arranged in two transversal rows, anteriorly without setae. Tenaculum with 4 + 4 teeth and one seta. Anterior furcal subcoxae with 15–17, posterior one with 8 setae. Anterior side of manubrium with 2 + 2 (more rarely with 3 + 2 or 3 + 3) setae (
<figureCitation box="[926,1088,1503,1527]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[144,211,1210,1232]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1178]" captionTargetId="figure-153@10.[144,1104,168,1178]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 5. Aggressopygus sibiricus sp. nov.: (A,B) furca, anterior (A) and lateral (B) views; (C) maxillary head; (D) tibiotarsus 3; (E,F) labrum, variation; (G) anterior part of the head; (H) apical row of labral setae, ventral view; (I) anterior side of manubrium, specimen from mountainous Shoria." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5195067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5195067/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1844">Figure 5A, 5I</figureCitation>
). Posterior side of manubrium with 5 + 5 laterobasal setae and 11 + 11 on main part, with 2 + 2 setae on lateral edges. Dens with 19–23 anterior setae. Posterior side of dens crenulated and with 5 normal setae (3 basal and 2 at the middle) and one rudimentary minute seta near base of mucro (
<figureCitation box="[667,809,1631,1655]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[144,211,1210,1232]" captionTargetBox="[144,1104,168,1178]" captionTargetId="figure-153@10.[144,1104,168,1178]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 5. Aggressopygus sibiricus sp. nov.: (A,B) furca, anterior (A) and lateral (B) views; (C) maxillary head; (D) tibiotarsus 3; (E,F) labrum, variation; (G) anterior part of the head; (H) apical row of labral setae, ventral view; (I) anterior side of manubrium, specimen from mountainous Shoria." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5195067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5195067/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1844">Figure 5A,B</figureCitation>
). Mucro short, bidentate. Manubrium about half as long as dens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
